      • removeLocation

        public boolean removeLocation(Location location)
                       throws SBOLValidationException
        Removes the given Location instance from the list of Location instances.

        If this SequenceAnnotation instance belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        location - the Location instance
        Returns:
        true if the matching Location instance is removed successfully, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if the following SBOL validation rule was violated: 10902

      • setComponent

        public void setComponent(String displayId)
                  throws SBOLValidationException
        Sets the reference Component URI to the URI of the Component instance matching the given displayId.

        If this SequenceAnnotation instance belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        This method creates a compliant URI for the reference Component instance using the persistent identity of this SequenceAnnotation instance's parent ComponentDefinition instance, the given displayId, and the parent ComponentDefinition instance's version. It then calls setComponent(URI) to set the reference.

        Parameters:
        displayId - the given display ID for the referenced component
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - see SBOLValidationException
